		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 11/12/1999 9:48:00 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=119&FN=General+Skills&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=371043&TN=Master+Beggars&CAT=Trade+Skills&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=371050&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I'm not sure whether to class it as an ability or a trade skill, but it goes up with use, not level. The more you use it, the more likely you are to increase it, much like sense heading.  There is a risk that the NPC you beg from will attack you for it, and then it's run or die. You *COULD* put 20pts into it at your guild, but this seems a LARGE waste of training points. If you're a caster, you can practice begging from your pet while sitting on your ass meditating. Your pet will never give you anything, but it will never attack you either. I'm sure it thinks less of you by the time you're ready to send it in to fight from you, but it IS your slave, right?<P>Sad to hear that at master begging skill, you STILL get nothing. We might need to start a petition to get the BEGGING SKILL FIXED!!!<P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
